data.name: ckLegacyBrowser.ToolTip
data.value:
Legacy Reconnect Method (Compatibility)
Right now, Tersebut is using new algorithm to reconnect wifi.id, allowing user to reconnect faster and low overhead. Yet this is still experimental, you can always backward into old algorithm that already proven to be working.
Note : This should be keep disabled and continue use the new one, unless the new algorithm really wrecks the reconnection.

data.name: numTolerance.ToolTip
data.value:
Reconnect Tolerance (in ping interval miliseconds)
Defines how long RTO program tolerate to reconnect. Lower values makes program is sensitive to reconnect but gives less delay to reconnect. Higher values makes program less sensitive to reconnect, lowering risk to false reconnection, but might takes longer delay to reconnect if login expires.

data.name: numTimeSafe.ToolTip
data.value:
TimeSafe Timeout (in second)
Defines how long program will prevent program to reconnect after last successful reconnection.This is used for low signal wifi that program might force to reconnect because false detection of login expiration.

data.name: Label6.Text
data.value:
Tersebut Reconnector is a program to enable user to reconnect their wifi connection when connected to access point known as @wifi.id, free@wifi.id, speedyInstan@wifi.id, and several Telkom wireless products that acquire login to connect and dropped every frequent time.
Tersebut is not affiliated by referenced corporation such as Telkomsel or Telkom, as this program is only a third-party helper software.
